=== Step 3: Upstream prebuilt Android-Vulkan release research ===

Repository: ggml-org/llama.cpp (formerly ggerganov/llama.cpp; still resolves)
Latest release at time of check: b8840 (2026-04-18)
Binary on device reports: version 1 (3f7c29d), Clang 18.0.3, Android aarch64
  (matches upstream CPU-only android tarball; 3f7c29d is the pre-release tag
   commit shown in llama-cli --version for this build channel.)

All assets for b8840 (relevant lines):
  llama-b8840-bin-android-arm64.tar.gz            63 MB   (CPU-only)
  llama-b8840-bin-ubuntu-vulkan-arm64.tar.gz      25 MB   (Linux glibc, NOT Android)
  llama-b8840-bin-ubuntu-vulkan-x64.tar.gz        (x86-64 Linux)
  llama-b8840-bin-win-opencl-adreno-arm64.zip     (Windows-ARM, Adreno-only)
  llama-b8840-bin-win-vulkan-x64.zip              (Windows x86-64)
  (no llama-b8840-bin-android-*-vulkan.* asset)
  (no llama-b8840-bin-android-*-opencl.*  asset)

Release workflow (.github/workflows/release.yml) android-arm64 job runs:
  -DCMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE=${ANDROID_NDK}/build/cmake/android.toolchain.cmake
  -DANDROID_ABI=arm64-v8a
  -DANDROID_PLATFORM=android-28
  (NO -DGGML_VULKAN=ON, NO -DGGML_OPENCL=ON)
Release page explicitly labels it "Android arm64 (CPU)".

CI build matrix (.github/workflows/build-android.yml) ships:
  - arm64-cpu
  - arm64-snapdragon (Hexagon NPU preset — Snapdragon only, N/A to Tensor G5)
No arm64-vulkan Android target is built or published by upstream.

Historical check: b8798 (2026-04-15, 3 days earlier) had NO android asset at
all. Android prebuilts only started at b8838 (2026-04-18). No prior release
ever shipped an Android Vulkan zip/tarball.

=== Step 3 conclusion ===
No prebuilt Android+Vulkan (or Android+OpenCL) llama.cpp binary exists
upstream. Going GPU on Pixel 6 requires building from source with the
Android NDK + Vulkan SDK, toolchain: android-ndk r26+, shaderc / glslc,
-DGGML_VULKAN=ON -DANDROID_ABI=arm64-v8a -DANDROID_PLATFORM=android-28.
This is a compile step, and per constraints we did NOT attempt it.

